# How to Create a USB Bootloader on Chrome OS

This guide will help you create a bootable USB stick for Chrome OS recovery or installation.

---

## Prerequisites

- A USB drive (at least 8GB recommended)
- A computer running Chrome OS (Chromebook)
- Internet connection
- Chrome browser

---

## Steps

### 1. Download the Chromebook Recovery Utility

1. Open the Chrome browser.
2. Go to the [Chrome Web Store](https://chrome.google.com/webstore).
3. Search for “Chromebook Recovery Utility” and install it.

### 2. Prepare Your USB Drive

- Plug the USB drive into your Chromebook.

### 3. Launch the Recovery Utility

1. Open the “Chromebook Recovery Utility” from your Apps.
2. Click “Get started”.

### 4. Identify Your Chromebook

- Enter your Chromebook model number or select it from the list.

### 5. Create the Recovery Media

1. Select your USB drive from the list.
2. Click “Continue” and follow the prompts.
3. Wait for the process to complete (this will erase the USB drive).

### 6. Boot from USB

- Plug the USB into the Chromebook you want to recover.
- Enter recovery mode (Esc + Refresh + Power).
- Follow on-screen instructions.

---

## Alternative: Using Linux Command Line

If you have a Chrome OS device in developer mode or access to Linux:

1. Download a Chrome OS recovery image (`.bin` file) from [Google’s site](https://support.google.com/chromeos/answer/1080595?hl=en).
2. Open a terminal.
3. Use the following script or commands (see `create_bootable_usb.sh`).

---

## Notes

- Creating the recovery USB will erase its contents.
- If your Chromebook won’t boot, use this USB stick to recover it.

---

